Class ec.e.inspect.Field 

java.lang.Object
   |
   +----ec.e.inspect.Field
public class Field
extends Object
A Field object carries type information about an instance variable in an object. It is derived from the class object (hence no actual instance is needed). In Java 1.1. Field objects can be retrieved from hooks in the JVM.
